### Workflow 4.4 — Bulk Update Bid

**Entry:** CPC Controls Dashboard

Step 1 → User clicks "Bulk Update Bid" button
Step 2 → System opens Bulk Update Bid panel/modal
Step 3 → Panel shows 5 fields: Floor CPC, Ceiling CPC, CPC Bid Multiplier, Ideal Floor CPC Override, Ideal Ceiling CPC Override
Step 4 → For each field, user selects update method from dropdown:
  - Option A: Set to absolute (sets all categories to this value)
  - Option B: Increase by (increments current values by amount)
  - Option C: Decrease by (decrements current values by amount)
Step 5 → User selects method for Floor CPC (e.g., "Set to absolute")
Step 6 → User enters value (e.g., 15)
Step 7 → User selects method for Ceiling CPC (e.g., "Increase by")
Step 8 → User enters increment value (e.g., 5)
Step 9 → User configures remaining fields as needed
Step 10 → User clicks Apply/Update
Step 11 → System applies bulk changes to all categories in the table
Step 12 → Review & Apply button becomes active
Step 13 → User clicks Review & Apply
Step 14 → "Category Bid Configurations Review" modal opens
Step 15 → Modal lists all affected categories and new values
Step 16 → User clicks Apply to confirm
✅ Workflow Complete — Bulk bid update applied to all categories

